# Development Workflow & Best Practices

## 10X Engineer Principles
- **Surgical Code**: Write minimal, precise code that solves the exact problem
- **Less is More**: Favor concise, readable solutions over verbose implementations
- **Quality First**: Every line should serve a purpose and be maintainable

## Development Commands
```bash
# Development server
pnpm dev

# Code quality checks
pnpm lint          # Check for issues
pnpm lint:fix      # Auto-fix issues
pnpm prettier      # Format code
pnpm test          # Run all quality checks

# Build and deployment
pnpm build         # Production build
pnpm start         # Production server
```

## Git Workflow
- **Pre-commit Hooks**: Automatic linting and formatting via lint-staged
- **Commit Standards**: Use conventional commit messages
- **Branch Strategy**: Feature branches with meaningful names

## Code Review Standards
- **Type Safety**: All code must pass TypeScript strict checks
- **Component Patterns**: Follow established component conventions
- **Performance**: Consider Server vs Client component implications
- **Accessibility**: Ensure WCAG compliance for UI components

## Environment Setup
- **Node.js**: Version >= 20 (specified in [package.json](mdc:package.json))
- **Package Manager**: pnpm (lockfile: [pnpm-lock.yaml](mdc:pnpm-lock.yaml))
- **Database**: Supabase local development via [supabase/config.toml](mdc:supabase/config.toml)

## Testing Strategy
- **Linting**: ESLint with Next.js and TypeScript rules
- **Formatting**: Prettier for consistent code style
- **Type Checking**: TypeScript compiler for type safety
- **Manual Testing**: Component functionality and user flows

## Performance Considerations
- **Server Components**: Default choice for better performance
- **Client Components**: Only when interactivity is required
- **Image Optimization**: Use Next.js Image component
- **Bundle Size**: Monitor and optimize package dependencies

## Security Practices
- **Environment Variables**: Secure API keys and secrets
- **Authentication**: Supabase session validation
- **API Security**: Request validation and error handling
- **Webhook Verification**: Signature validation for external webhooks

## Deployment Checklist
- [ ] TypeScript compilation passes
- [ ] ESLint checks pass
- [ ] Prettier formatting applied
- [ ] Environment variables configured
- [ ] Database migrations applied
- [ ] API endpoints tested
- [ ] Authentication flows verified